					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">LZ77 isn't as efficient as LZSS. Having to encode uncompressed data with run lengths can really bulk up smaller runs of data. I like LZSS +1bit per element of uncompress data method better. I don't think I've actually used the original spec of LZ77.
<br />
<br /> Not so much for NES, but SNES, Genesis, and  Turbo Duo and others that have WORD size tilemap elements really benefit from a variable elements size RLE system. One control code for BYTE RLE and another for WORD RLE.</div>

