				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Would it be worth it to try compressing some real data with LZSS and taking statistics on the distribution of literal run lengths?</div>I tried this when trying out different encodings for my packer. I didn't keep the statistics but gamma coding was a clear win on the files I tested, not that it made much of a difference either way (perhaps a single percent or so.)</div>

